				<p>@AndrewCapodieci I'm not sure why you changed your mind on your original answer.  Any brushless motor can indeed be microstepped just like a stepper motor.  Stepper motors are built to have very small "full" steps and will have a different configuration but the principles still apply.  The open loop performance for both also depends on the load, friction and variation from the spec.  In closed loop brushless and steppers can be controlled to extremely fine angular positioning (pretty much as fine as your feedback).</p>
